<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
The genus 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Berberis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Berberis" order="Ranunculales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Berberis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (including 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapotaceae" genus="Mahonia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mahonia" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Mahonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nutt.) comprises ca. 650 species of shrubs or small trees that are not very widespread in the Northern hemisphere. In the Neotropics its distribution is limited to mountainous regions. In South America it reaches Tierra del Fuego and south-eastern Brazil. In these regions only species with simple (not compound) leaves are recorded (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1095-8339.1961.tb00889.x" author="Ahrendt, LWA" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 410" refId="B1" refString="Ahrendt, LWA, 1961. Berberis and Mahonia: A taxonomic revision. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 57 (369): 1 - 410, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1095-8339.1961.tb00889.x" title="Berberis and Mahonia: A taxonomic revision." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1095-8339.1961.tb00889.x" volume="57" year="1961">Ahrendt 1961</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2666170" author="Landrum, L" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="793 - 834" refId="B28" refString="Landrum, L, 1999. Revision of Berberis (Berberidaceae) in Chile and adjacent southern Argentina. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 86 (4): 793 - 834, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2666170" title="Revision of Berberis (Berberidaceae) in Chile and adjacent southern Argentina." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2666170" volume="86" year="1999">Landrum 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ulloa Ulloa, C" journalOrPublisher="Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" publicationUrl="http://www.kew.org/science/tropamerica/neotropikey/families/Berberidaceae.htm" refId="B50" refString="Ulloa Ulloa, C, 2009. Neotropical Berberidaceae. In: Milliken W, Klitgard B, Baracat A (2009 onwards), Neotropikey - Interactive key and information resources for flowering plants of the Neotropics. http://www.kew.org/science/tropamerica/neotropikey/families/Berberidaceae.htm" title="Neotropical Berberidaceae. In: Milliken W, Klitgard B, Baracat A (2009 onwards), Neotropikey - Interactive key and information resources for flowering plants of the Neotropics." url="http://www.kew.org/science/tropamerica/neotropikey/families/Berberidaceae.htm" year="2009">Ulloa Ulloa 2009</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Berberis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Berberis multiflora" order="Ranunculales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multiflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Berberis multiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Benth. (synonyms: 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. loxensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="loxensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">B. loxensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Benth., 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. warszewiczii" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="warszewiczii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">B. warszewiczii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hieron. and 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. multiflora subsp. var. var. calvescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="variety" species="multiflora" subSpecies="var." variety="calvescens">B. multiflora var. calvescens</taxonomicName>
C.K. Schneid.; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ulloa Ulloa, C" editor="Jorgensen, PM" journalOrPublisher="Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="319 - 320" refId="B49" refString="Ulloa Ulloa, C, 1999. Berberidaceae. In: Jorgensen, PM, Leon-Yanez, S, Eds., Catalogue of Vascular plants of Ecuador. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 75: 319 - 320" title="Berberidaceae." volume="75" volumeTitle="Catalogue of Vascular plants of Ecuador." year="1999">Ulloa Ulloa 1999</bibRefCitation>
), which is one such species, is native to Ecuador and Peru (
<bibRefCitation author="Brako, L" journalOrPublisher="Monographs in systematic botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 1286" refId="B9" refString="Brako, L, Zarucchi, JL, 1993. Catalogue of the flowering plants and gymnosperms of Peru: Catalogo de las angiospermas y gimnospermas del Peru. Monographs in systematic botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 45: 1 - 1286" title="Catalogue of the flowering plants and gymnosperms of Peru: Catalogo de las angiospermas y gimnospermas del Peru." volume="45" year="1993">Brako and Zarucchi 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ulloa Ulloa, C" editor="Jorgensen, PM" journalOrPublisher="Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="319 - 320" refId="B49" refString="Ulloa Ulloa, C, 1999. Berberidaceae. In: Jorgensen, PM, Leon-Yanez, S, Eds., Catalogue of Vascular plants of Ecuador. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 75: 319 - 320" title="Berberidaceae." volume="75" volumeTitle="Catalogue of Vascular plants of Ecuador." year="1999">Ulloa Ulloa 1999</bibRefCitation>
). The species is considered to be morphologically very variable. However, studying numerous type specimens (syntypes) of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. multiflora" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="multiflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">B. multiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected by 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Hartweg 708</emphasis>
in Peru (one of them, mounted to the sheet with stamp Herbarium Benthamianum 1854, K 407116!, is here designated as lectotype), we noticed that they somewhat differ from these representing 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. warszewiczii" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="warszewiczii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">B. warszewiczii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(F! negative no. 14317, https://fm-digital-assets.fieldmuseum.org/30/341/14317.jpg, KRA). The main difference between the two species concerns the leaf morphology. In the case of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. warszewiczii" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="warszewiczii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">B. warszewiczii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, leaf edge (excluding the base) is regularly spine-toothed while leaves of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. multiflora" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="multiflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">B. multiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are entire, or with a few spines. However, during the revision of specimens representing 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. multiflora" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="multiflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">B. multiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we noticed several specimens with spine-toothed leaves, what makes them more similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. warszewiczii" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="warszewiczii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">B. warszewiczii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or even to 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. pectinata" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="pectinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">B. pectinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Revision using molecular analyses is needed in this group of taxa to explain their taxonomic relationship. Bearing in mind that the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. warszewiczii" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="warszewiczii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">B. warszewiczii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hieron. at B was destroyed, we designated here the specimen collected by Warszewicz and preserved at KRA as the lectotype and the two additional (KRA 533000, KRA 533001) as the isolectotypes. The specimens preserved in KRA are duplicates of the type documented on 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Macbride’s">Macbride's</normalizedToken>
photograph (F negative no. 14317, https://fm-digital-assets.fieldmuseum.org/28/661/14317.jpg), and their morphology matches with the description of the taxon.
</paragraph>
